        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Lucky to be able to afford a similar attitude. I’m an introvert with occasional bursts of sociability, so consistently hustling as an average Indie Hacker does is a road to burn out for me. And I won’t survive a month in the rhythm of the Marketing Course Gurus. x_x</p>
<p>But the gardening approach often requires some backup income. In my case, I spent years working for clients for a few months and then trying whatever project until money started running out.</p>
